value.0: Fashioned from rough iron, these bars extend into a narrow slot in the floor.
Fashioned from rough-hewn wood, this simple door swings on ill-fitting hinges.
This Area is set up for the purpuse of facilitating beta testing.  Through the doors lie areas that could use beta testing for either asthetic or debuging purposes.
A number of dwarves in an ale hall start up a round of that catchy Dwarf and Orc song.  Speak with the dwarf on the left and tell him that you think the place is a little dead.
A pacing merchant is willing to pay gold if you lend him a hand.
Crazy old hag in the forest offers to make a potion for you if you get her a number of ingredients.

Speak with the merchant and accept the quest he offers.  Then find out how to get to The dwarven Mines.

Note: Remember gold isnt always the best way to be rewarded.

This should hopefully be technicaly debuged but if some one could write directions to the dwarven mines i would be very greatfull.  Im just too lazy to figure it out...
This script controlls who gets to get in to see the thane of the mines or speak with his treasurer
A scripted sceen conserning a druid moonpool could use some feedback on it as its still being worked on.
This series of scripts controlls traffic flow in several of the inns in the moonshaes.  Could use feedback on its asthetic qualities and or if it seems to cause anyone lag.
A quirkey gnome imagrent thats set up shop in corwell.  There are a number of scripts associated with him that could use testing.
I got bored and wanted to try something.  Sit down on Odens chairs and see what happens.
Own your own horse.  By far teh coolest thing ive seen here yet kudos to who ever made this thing!
Horse Stables Buy/Own your own Horse ICly
Speak to the Dwarf ahead of you.  Get a pick axe and head down into the mines to look for your fortune.
At night a local bard on hammerstaad will gather with children around a camp fire and tell them stories when a PC gets close enough.
Wino The Story Teller ((only shows up at night time))
